Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art, taken at an angle, showing figures of at least two boats, an unidentified quadruped, canid, cow and arc-shaped boats. Largest figure is that at right of unidentified quadruped, schematic, pecked in outline, upright and facing right ,with exaggerated neck. To lower left of this possibly a canid standing below an arc-shaped boat. Further large arc is at lower centre. Largest arc is in foreground at left, showing boat, with cow and further boat with oars pointing up below it. Alec Campbell seen at lower right recording rock art. Eastern Desert, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
